&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;印第安那大学与普渡大学印第安那波里斯联合分校(Indiana University-Purdue University Indianapolis，简称IUPUI) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;方晓芬教授学术报告会&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告内容：1、学术报告：&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visualization of Human Brain Connectome &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;、海外留学、海外博士后岗位介绍 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告时间：2015年12月4日下午2:30-3:30&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告地点：民主楼小礼堂&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告人:&lt;/strong&gt;Prof. Shiaofen Fang, Department of Computer &amp;amp; Information Science, Indiana University Purdue University Indianapolis&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告摘要：&lt;/strong&gt;Visualization plays a vital role in the analysis of multi-modal neuroimaging data. A major challenge in neuroimaging visualization is how to integrate structural, functional and connectivity data to form a comprehensive visual context for data exploration, quality control, and hypothesis discovery. In this talk I will present some of our recent work on integrated visualization solution for brain imaging data by combining scientific and information visualization techniques within the context of brain anatomic structures. Several techniques will be discussed including (1) a multi-modal neuroimaging visualization tool, (2) a new surface texture technique for attribute mapping and disease features detection, (3) a new spherical volume rendering technique for generating interactive brain maps, and (4) a multi-graph technique for feature detection. This integrated visualization solution can help neuroscientists identify correlated brain regions, their activity patterns, and disease related brain connection features and imaging phenotype biomarkers. &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告人简介：&lt;/strong&gt;Dr. Shiaofen Fang is a Professor of Computer Science and the Chairman of the Department of Computer and Information Science at Indiana University Purdue University Indianapolis (IUPUI). Prof. Fang received his Ph.D in Computer Science from the University of Utah and his BS and MS in Mathematics from Zhejiang University. Prof. Fang’s research interest is in Scientific and Information Visualization, Medical Imaging, Volume Graphics, and Geometric Modeling. He has published extensively in these fields. His research has been funded by the National Science Foundation (NSF), Nation Institutes of Health (NIH), National Institute of Justice (NIJ) and US Department of Defense (DoD). He is a regular panelists and reviewers for NSF and NIH, and has chaired or served in program committees in many international conferences and workshops.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告时间：&lt;/strong&gt;10月9号（星期五）下午4:00 - 5:40&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告地点：&lt;/strong&gt;中南大学校本部计算机楼212会议室&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告：&lt;/strong&gt;英国埃塞克斯大学（University of Essex）Kun Yang教授 —Wireless Information and Energy Cooperation（无线网络中信息和能量的联合传送）&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告简介：&lt;/strong&gt;移动互联网使得我们生活的很多方面变得更加无线和移动，但是还没有在电能传递方面，至少没有在足够长的距离为我们至爱的智能手机无线充电。这个讲座将给大家介绍无线输电的基本知识、信息和能量联合传送的基本原理和准则（如能量使用的上下边界），并在此基础上介绍我们提出的一个无线网络中的能量分割算法。注意：这里的关键是如何使我们的手机在上网的同时自动无线充电！&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;The world is going wireless and mobile but not energy transferring yet, at least not at a reasonably long distance and for our beloved everyday companion – mobile phones! Researchers from both academia and industries have put much effort in achieving this goal. Starting from some introduction of the basics of wireless power transfer (WPT) covering its applications and principles the Talk moves on to a brand new and more exciting field of wireless information and energy cooperation, i.e., transmitting information and energy simultaneously and wirelessly. Again some basic principles are presented here including the theoretical upper and lower bounds for energy consumption used by information delivery. Finally the Talk presents a fair power splitting algorithm proposed by the Speaker and his Team. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告人简介：&lt;/strong&gt;Kun Yang (杨鲲) obtained his PhD from the Department of Electronic &amp;amp; Electrical Engineering of University College London (UCL), UK, and his MSc and BSc degrees were both from Jilin University. He is currently a Chair Professor and the Head of Network Convergence Laboratory (NCL) in the School of Computer Science and Electronic Engineering, University of Essex, UK. Before joining in University of Essex at 2003, he worked at UCL on several EU research projects such as FAIN, MANTRIP, CONTEXT in the area of IP network management, active networks and context-aware services. Now his main research interests focus on heterogeneous wireless networks，future Internet architecture and its technologies such as network virtualization, software defined networking (wired and wireless), smart grid, etc. He has published more than 80 journal papers and books, in addition to 60+ major conference papers. He manages research projects funded by EU FP7/H2020 (such as the EVANS, iCIRRUS projects), EPSRC (e.g., PANDA, PAL, DANCER), and industries such as British Telecom (e.g., MOSE). He serves on the editorial boards of both IEEE and non-IEEE journals (Wiley or Springer). He is a Senior Member of IEEE and a Fellow of IET.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;Homepage:&lt;a&gt;http://privatewww.essex.ac.uk/~kunyang/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;新加坡资讯科技研究院刘江博士学术报告通知&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;报告时间：2015年12月4日下午3:30 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;报告地点：民主楼小礼堂 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;报告题目：Computer Vision and Digital Image Processing - Concepts and Applications&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;计算机视觉和数字图像处理－概念和应用 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;报告简介：简单介绍计算机视觉和数字图像处理相关概念，及其与人类视觉的关系。同时着重介绍计算机视觉和数字图像技术在医疗，无人车导航及卫星图像处理方面的应用。 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Bio: Dr.Jimmy Liu is the founding head of ocular imaging iMED program in the institute for infocomm research. In 2013,Jimmy established AVATA clinical research joint lab with Singapore National Health Group and ATLANTIA industrial joint research lab with Japanese TOPCON Corporation. Translational and licensing efforts of the ocular image research are greatly boosted through the AVATA (I2R and National Health Group Advanced Vision and Technology Alliance) and ATLANTIA (Advanced Technological Laboratory for A*STAR and TOPCON Innovation Alliance) joint labs. He is also the adjunct associate professor in SCE,NTU, Adjunct Principle Scientist in Singapore Eye Research Institute and the Singapore Chapter Chair for IEEE EMBS (Engineering in Medicine &amp;amp; Biology Society). &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;个人简介：刘江博士系新加坡资讯科技研究院视觉医疗影像所首届技术所长。他又与2013年创立与新加坡国家健宝集团的合作中心，及与日本TOPCON公司的第一个海外合作中心。并任两个中心的主任。他同时是新加坡南洋理工大学的兼职副教授，新加坡眼科中心兼职首席科学家，新加坡.IEEE生物医学新加坡分部主席。主要研究方向为基于医疗图像的眼科疾病诊断等。发表了100多篇学术文章，申请了10余项国际专利。 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;“智力引进计划”石碰教授学术报告通知 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告时间：&lt;/strong&gt;12月9号（星期三）上午9:30 - 10:30&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告地点：&lt;/strong&gt;中南大学校本部民主楼小礼堂&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker&lt;/strong&gt;:澳大利亚阿德莱德大学石碰教授&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title&lt;/strong&gt;: Fuzzy Control Systems with Time-Delay and Stochastic Perturbation: Analysis and Synthesis&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a&gt;石碰教授简介：石碰教授现任澳大利亚阿德莱德大学电气与电子学院教授&lt;/a&gt;,主要研究方向是系统与控制理论、计算智能和运筹学等。石碰教授是众多学会的会士,包括IEEE Fellow, IET Fellow, IMA Fellow等，担任国际学术期刊《International Journal of Innovative Computing Information and Control》主编，《International Journal of Nonlinear Dynamics and Systems Theory》区域主编，并担任多个国际顶级学术刊物的顾问或编委，包括《Automatica》、《IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control,《IEEE Transactions on Circuits and Systems-I》、《IEEE Transactions on Cybernetics》、《IEEE Transactions on Fuzzy Systems》、《IEEE Access》、《Signal Processing》、《&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a&gt;Circuits Systems and Signal Processing&lt;/a&gt;》、《Information Sciences》、《International Journal of Systems Science》、《Journal of the Franklin Institute》、《Journal of Intelligent and Fuzzy Systems》等。石碰教授团队每年发表50余篇国际期刊论文，很多发表在IEEE Transactions汇刊、&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a&gt;Automatica&lt;/a&gt;、SIAM Journals等权威期刊上，其中2015年已发表或在线发表IEEE Transactions汇刊、Automatica论文40余篇。石教授十余年来一直是ISI Thomson Reuters高引论文科学家（2002-2014）。 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;美国佩斯大学（&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pace University&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;）&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meikang Qiu&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;副教授&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;学术报告通知&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告时间：&lt;/strong&gt;12月18日（星期五）下午4:00 - 5:30&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告地点：&lt;/strong&gt;中南大学校本部计算机楼212会议室&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告：&lt;/strong&gt;美国佩斯大学（Pace University）Meikang Qiu副教授 —Privacy Protection for Mobile Cloud to Prevent Data Over-collection&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告简介：&lt;/strong&gt;In smart city, all kinds of users’ data are stored in electronic devices to make everything intelligent. A smartphone is the most widely used electronic device and it is the pivot of all smart systems. However, current smartphones are not competent to manage users’ sensitive data, and they are facing the privacy leakage caused by data over-collection. Data over-collection, which means smartphones apps collect users’ data more than its original function while within the permission scope, is rapidly becoming one of the most serious potential security hazards in smart city. We study the current state of data over-collection and study some most frequent data over-collected cases. We present a mobile-cloud framework, which is an active approach to eradicate the data over-collection. By putting all users’ data into a cloud, the security of users’ data can be greatly improved. We have done extensive experiments and the experimental results have demonstrated the effectiveness of our approach. This research has been published in IEEE Transactions on Computers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告人简介：&lt;/strong&gt;Meikang Qiu received the BE and ME degrees from Shanghai Jiao Tong University and received Ph.D. degree of Computer Science from University of Texas at Dallas. Currently, he is an Associate Professor of Computer Science at Pace University.He is an IEEE Senior member and ACM Senior member. His research interests include cyber security, cloud computing, big data storage, hybrid memory, heterogeneous systems, embedded systems, operating systems, optimization, intelligent systems, sensor networks, etc. A lot of novel results have been produced and most of them have already been reported to research community through high-quality journal and conference papers. He has published 5 books, 300 peer-reviewed journal and conference papers (including 140+ journal articles, 160+ conference papers, 40+ IEEE/ACM Transactions papers), and 3 patents. He has won ACM Transactions on Design Automation of Electrical Systems (TODAES) 2011 Best Paper Award. His paper about cloud computing has been published in JPDC (Journal of Parallel and Distributed Computing, Elsevier) and ranked #1 in Top Hottest 25 Papers of JPDC 2012. He has won another 8 Conference Best Paper Awards in recent years. Currently he is an associate editor of 10+ international journals, including IEEE Transactions on Computers and IEEE Transactions on Cloud Computing. He is the General Chair/Program Chair of a dozen of IEEE/ACM international conferences, such as IEEE HPCC, IEEE CSCloud, IEEE BigDataSecurity. He has given 100+ talks all over the world, including Oxford, Princeton, Stanford, and New York University. He has won Navy Summer Faculty Award in 2012 and Air Force Summer Faculty Award in 2009. His research is supported by US government such as NSF, Air Force, Navy and companies such as GE, Nokia, TCL, and Cavium.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;Homepage:&lt;a&gt;http://csis.pace.edu/~mqiu/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;香港理工大学&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Yixin Cao&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;博士学术报告通知&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告题目&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;：&lt;/strong&gt;Modular Decomposition and its Algorithmic Applications &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告时间：&lt;/strong&gt;2016年1月4&lt;a&gt;日下午&lt;/a&gt;4点 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告地点：&lt;/strong&gt;升华后楼215 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告摘要&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;：&lt;/strong&gt;Birds of a Feather Flock Together. A similar observation in graphs is that some vertices are ``alike&apos;&apos;: A set of vertices is a module if they have the same neighborhood outside this set, and they can be treated as a whole for many problems. A nice theory has been built on the properties of modules, and in particular, all the modules of a graph can be represented by a hierarchical tree structure. This provides a very handy, and sometimes indispensable, tool for solving a large family of graph problems. We survey the use of modules in bioinformatics and social networks, including both classic results and our recent ones. &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告人简介：&lt;/strong&gt;Dr. Yixin Cao is an Assistant Professor of Computing at Hong Kong Polytechnic University. He received the Ph.D. degree in computer science from Texas A&amp;amp;M University, USA in 2012. Before coming back to China, Dr. Cao was a research fellow at Institute for Computer Science and Control, Hungarian Academy of Sciences. He has been visiting scholar in Institute for Computational and Experimental Research in Mathematics (ICERM), Brown University. &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;His research interests are in graph algorithms, combinatorial optimization, and their usages in bioinformatics and social networks. His research is supported by Hong Kong RGC ECS award and NSFC. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告时间：&lt;/strong&gt;11月17号（星期二）上午8:30 - 9:30 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告地点：&lt;/strong&gt;中南大学校本部计算机楼212会议室&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告：&lt;/strong&gt;台湾大学（National Taiwan University）Sy-Yen Kuo教授、IEEE Fellow—Selected Threats and Challenges for Dependable Systems &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告简介：&lt;/strong&gt;With the advent of Internet of Things (IoT) technology, the networked devices pervade every aspect of our daily life. Therefore, we are facing more serious threats to the dependability of systems and information due to problems caused by accidental events such as human mistakes and physical malfunctions or by intentional behavior being either malicious or non-malicious. In this talk, we will discuss some example threats and challenges for systems requiring high dependability. We then give views of future directions in research on the dependability of networked systems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告人简介：&lt;/strong&gt;Sy-Yen Kuo is a Distinguished Professor at the Department of Electrical Engineering, National Taiwan University (NTU), Taipei, Taiwan. He was the Dean of College of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science in NTU from 2012 to 2015 and the Chairman of Department of Electrical Engineering in NTU from 2001 to 2004. He also took a leave from NTU and served as a Chair Professor and Dean of the College of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science, National Taiwan University of Science and Technology from 2006 to 2009. He received the BS (1979) in Electrical Engineering from National Taiwan University, the MS (1982) in Electrical &amp;amp; Computer Engineering from the University of California at Santa Barbara, and the PhD (1987) in Computer Science from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. He spent his sabbatical years as a Visiting Professor at Hong Kong Polytechnic University from 2011-2012 and at the Chinese University of Hong Kong from 2004-2005, and as a visiting researcher at AT&amp;amp;T Labs-Research, New Jersey from 1999 to 2000, respectively. He was a faculty member in the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering at the University of Arizona from 1988 to 1991, and an engineer at Fairchild Semiconductor and Silvar-Lisco, both in California, from 1982 to 1984. In 1989, he also worked as a summer faculty fellow at Jet Propulsion Laboratory of California Institute of Technology. His current research interests include dependable systems and networks, mobile computing, cloud computing, and quantum computing and communications. Professor Kuo is an IEEE Fellow. He has published more than 400 papers in journals and conferences, and also holds 18 US patents, 12 Taiwan patents, and several patents other countries. He received the Distinguished Research Award and the Distinguished Research Fellow award from the National Science Council, Taiwan. He was also a recipient of the Best Paper Award in the 1996 International Symposium on Software Reliability Engineering, the Best Paper Award in the simulation and test category at the 1986 IEEE/ACM Design Automation Conference (DAC), the National Science Foundation&apos;s Research Initiation Award in 1989, and the IEEE/ACM Design Automation Scholarship in 1990 and 1991.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;Homepage:&lt;a&gt;http://www.ee.ntu.edu.tw/profile?id=29&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;中南大学名师名家学术论坛通知&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;论坛主题：&lt;/strong&gt;美国工程教育简介——从历史说起（Engineering Education in United States）&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;论坛时间：&lt;/strong&gt;2015年10月14日14:30～16:00&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;论坛地点：&lt;/strong&gt;中南大学铁道校区世纪楼C座201国际报告厅&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;论坛主持人：&lt;/strong&gt;电子与通信工程系主任李宏 教授&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;人&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;：&lt;/strong&gt;美国中佛罗里达大学Kuo-ChiLin教授&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告简介：&lt;/strong&gt;In United States, when engineering students are asked why did they choose their majors?The typical answers are: because I like to work on, for example, automobiles, robots, computers, satellites, etc. Many of them even have had some hands-on experiences before entering college.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;However, once they are in the Engineering colleges, they find that most of the courses are very theoretical and general, with a heavy emphasis on sciences and mathematics. When they graduate, the universities ask them to do a survey to give feedback to their schools.The most common complain about the Engineering curriculum is the lack of “practical courses”. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;InUnited States, the Federal government does not decide the education curricula for any level of schools. The standards and requirements for Engineering colleges are set by a non-government accreditation organization—ABET.The members of ABET consist most of the professional engineer associations, such as IEEE, ASME, AIAA, etc. The curriculum standards and requirements for each Engineering degree program are decided by the corresponding engineer association. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The college education inUnitedStateis leaning toward “general education”, not “vocational education”. This philosophy originated from the 17-centuryWestern Europeuniversities.The ABET accreditation criteria consist: “The students should be able to apply mathematics, science, and engineering principles (to solve engineering problems).” &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;This talk starts with the reviewing of the American education history, from colonial era to the 20&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;Century. The evolution of the Engineering education has to do with the needs of the nation at different times in the American history.An introduction of the ABET accreditation process will also be included.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告人简介：&lt;/strong&gt;Dr. Lin received his PhD in Aerospace Engineering fromUniversityofMichiganin 1990.In the same year, he joined University of Central Florida (UCF) as a joint-faculty between Institute for Simulation and Training (IST) and Department of Mechanical and Aerospace Engineering (MAE). Between 2006 and 2014, Dr. Lin served as the Associate Chair of the MAE department.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Dr. Lin has published over 125 technical papers in the peer-reviewed journals and conference proceeding.He has received 3.4 million US dollars research funding as the Principle Investigator (PI) or Co-PI. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;In the 25-year teaching career, Dr. Lin has been involved in the ABET accreditation many times.The 8-year service as the Associate Chair makes him very familiar with the curricula and the students. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

