&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;题目&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;：&lt;/strong&gt;大数据分析与处理技术在大电网中的应用&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告时间：&lt;/strong&gt;2015年11月27日下午4点&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告地点：&lt;/strong&gt;民主楼小礼堂 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告简介：&lt;/strong&gt;在大数据分析中，数据可分为1）静态数据(Data at Rest)；2）动态数据(Data in motion)两大类。静态数据分析关注数据储存、数据挖掘等方面的问题，动态数据分析关注高速流式数据处理及复杂事件即时处理问题。在实际大数据分析问题中，通常需要采用静态数据分析和动态数据分析相结合的方法。用静态数据分析方法研究物理系统态势（模型、参数及演变模式），用动态数据分析方法感知（监测）物理系统态势。本次研讨将讨论大数据分析及用于流数据分析的复杂事件处理（CEP）技术中一些基本概念，以及CEP技术在大电网快速在线安稳分析中的应用。&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告人简介：&lt;/strong&gt;Michael Zhou (周二专)，博士（清华大学、1987），国家第十期千人计划专家，国家电网电力科学研究院首席专家。先后在美国、加拿大多所知名大学开展电力系统方面博士后研究和教学工作。1996年在将面向对象的编程方法引入电力系统仿真。回国前担任国际知名中间件产品提供商—美国TIBCO公司的高级架构师,是SOA、EDA、ESB、CEP等方面设计和实施专家，曾为美国和世界多家银行、保险公司实施SOA、EDA和ESB提供咨询和解决方案。国际开放式电网仿真软件InterPSS项目和ODM（Open Model for Power System Simulation Data Exchange）项目创立人，目前正着手开展大电网快速在线安稳分析软件系统研发工作。&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot; style=&quot;text-align: right&quot;&gt;信息科学与工程学院&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot; style=&quot;text-align: right&quot;&gt;2015.11.20&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;中南大学信息科学与工程学院研究生学术年会学术报告&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告题目&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aperspective on Industrially Applied PSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;主讲人：&lt;/strong&gt;芬兰Aalto&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a&gt;大学&lt;/a&gt;Sirkka-Liisa J&amp;auml;ms&amp;auml;-Jounela教授 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;时间：&lt;/strong&gt;2015年11月5日上午9：00~10:00 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;地点：&lt;/strong&gt;民主楼小礼堂 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;摘要&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;PSE, process systems engineering, is about the development and application of systematic methods for process design and control studies by the chemical engineer. By means of software tools, the application of these methods is facilitated. Over the last about half a century, CAPE (computer aided process engineering) tools have found their way into process engineering. E.g. nowadays it is unthinkable to design a plant without a simulation in a flow sheet package or its control strategies without modelling and control design tools. &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The integration of design and control, control and scheduling and design, control and scheduling, all have been core PSE challenges. While significant progress has been achieved over the years, it is fair to say that at the moment there is not a generally accepted methodology and/or “protocol” for such an integration - it is also interesting to note that currently, there is not a commercially available software [or even in a prototype form] system to fully support such an activity. But there are many more applications of PSE in industry. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;In this paper a (Finnish) perspective on industrially applied PSE is discussed. Finally industrial case studies in the area of process modelling, control and monitoring as well as fault diagnosis by the author’s group are presented and evaluated. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Sirkka-Liisa J&amp;auml;ms&amp;auml;-Jounela&lt;strong&gt;教授英文简介&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;：&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Sirkka-Liisa J&amp;auml;ms&amp;auml;-Jounela graduated from Oulu University of Technology in 1978 where she majored in process control. After graduation she worked as a software development engineer. In 1981 she continued her research work at the Electrical Engineering Laboratory of the Technical Research Centre of Finland , and received her Licentiate of Technology Degree from Helsinki University of Technology in 1985. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Prof. J&amp;auml;ms&amp;auml;-Jounela has gained practical experience in working for a number of companies in the Finnish process industry. In 1983 she joined Kemira Engineering and worked as a control engineer at the Siilinj&amp;auml;rvi phosphate plant. During 1987-1991 she was employed as a research scientist (industrial researcher) by the Academy of Finland and Kemira Oy. During 1987-1988 she was a visiting scholar at the Department of Metallurgical Engineer, University of Utah, USA, and received her doctoral degree from the Helsinki University of Technology in 1990. In 1991 she joined the Outokumpu Group, where she worked as a senior consultant and also received practical experience in international automation projects. Her main responsibility was designing the instrumentation and control systems and implementing and testing control strategies for the unit processes of mineral processing plants. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Prof. J&amp;auml;ms&amp;auml;-Jounela has also made MBA studies at the Helsinki School of Economics and Business Administration, at Glasgow University, United Kingdom and at the European Business School in Copenhagen, Denmark. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;She took up her current position as Professor in Process Control at the Helsinki University of Technology in 1994. The laboratory provides education in process automation, mainly in the fields of Chemical Technology, Forest Products Technology and Materials Science and Rock Engineering. Prof. J&amp;auml;ms&amp;auml;-Jounela has supervised over 180 MSc exams and about 15 PhD students. She has published over 200 international conference and journal papers, mainly on process control and automation. She has given numerous invited lectures and plenaries in international conferences and workshops. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Prof. J&amp;auml;ms&amp;auml;-Jounela began her affiliation with IFAC in 1992 as a member of the TC Automation in Mining, Mineral and Metal Processing, and in 1996 she was appointed Chair of this Technical Committee (1996-2002). She served as IFAC Vice President and Chair of the Technical Board. She has been the IPC chair in numerous events organized by IFAC and other international societies. She has also been the Chair of the Nordic Process Control Group and is the board member of the European Union Control Association. Prof. J&amp;auml;ms&amp;auml;-Jounela was the associate editor of the IEEE TCST and is a member of the Finnish Academy of Technologies. Currently she is serving Academy of Finland as aResearch Council Member for Natural Sciences and Engineering。 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 中南大学信息学院自动化科学与技术系 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_start&quot;&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a&gt;美国德州农工大学卡塔尔分校黄廷文教授和澳大利亚皇家墨尔本大学博士生李超杰学术报告通知 &lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告时间：&lt;/strong&gt;11月30号（星期一）上午9:00 - 11:30 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;报告地点：&lt;/strong&gt;中南大学校本部民主楼小礼堂&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker&lt;/strong&gt;:美国德州农工大学黄廷文教授，澳大利亚皇家墨尔本大学博士生李超杰 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title 1&lt;/strong&gt;:Discontinuous Control and Applications (Prof. Huang) &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract 1:&lt;/strong&gt;Chaos synchronization is important and useful in applied physics, electronic engineering, and biological sciences. In comparison with continuous control of chaos, the discontinuous control method, which includes impulsive control, occasional bang-bang control, occasional proportional feedback and intermittent control, has attracted more interest recently due to its easy implementation in engineering control. In this talk, the recent development of discontinuous control including impulsive and intermittent control will be addressed. &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title 2&lt;/strong&gt;:Efficient Computation for Sparse Load Shifting in Demand Side Management(Mr. Li) &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract 2:&lt;/strong&gt;In this talk, it introduces a distributed algorithm for sparse load shifting in demand-side management with a focus on the scheduling problem of residential smart appliances. Although there are many game theoretic models for the demand-side management problem, the computational efficiency of finding Nash equilibrium that globally minimizes the total energy consumption cost and the peak-to-average ratio is still an outstanding issue. We develop a bidirectional framework for solving the demand-side management problem in a distributed way to substantially improve the search efficiency. A Newton method is employed to accelerate the centralized coordination of demand side management strategies that superlinearly converge to a better Nash equilibrium minimizing the peak-to-average ratio. Furthermore, dual fast gradient and convex relaxation are applied to tackle the sub-problem for customers&apos; best response, which is able to relieve customers&apos; discomfort from load shifting or interrupting. Detailed results from illustrative case studies are presented and discussed, which shows the costs of energy consumption and daily peak demand by our algorithm are reduced. Finally, some conclusions are drawn. &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;黄廷文教授简介：黄廷文教授现任美国德州农工大学卡塔尔分校教授，主要从事混沌动力学、稳定性理论、神经网路与复杂网络、计算智能等研究，在国际重要刊物或会议上发表相关学术论文200余篇，主持或合作主持卡塔尔国家优先资助基金项目5项，是混沌系统和神经网络同步研究领域的国际知名学者，曾担任10多个国际重要会议的分会主席或程序委员会委员，现担任&lt;a&gt;IEEE Transactions on Neural Networks and Learning Systems&lt;/a&gt;等多个国际学术期刊编委，是美国数学会、美国工业与数学会会员。 &lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;vsbcontent_end&quot;&gt;李超杰简介：Mr. Li于2007、2011年在重庆大学分别获得电子科学与技术学士、计算机硕士学位，目前在澳大利亚皇家墨尔本大学攻读博士学位。他目前的研究兴趣包括：分布式优化与控制及其在智能电网中的应用，神经网络及其应用。研究成果发表在国际重要学术期刊或会议20余篇，SCI期刊10余篇，包括IEEE Transactions on&lt;a&gt;Industrial Informatics&lt;/a&gt;(2014年影响因子：8.785),&lt;a&gt;IEEE Transactions on Neural Networks and Learning Systems&lt;/a&gt;等。 &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
